
[1]gentile

   GEN'TILE, n. [L. gentilis; from L. gens, nation, race; applied to
   pagans.]

   In the scriptures, a pagan; a worshipper of false gods; any person not
   a Jew or a christian; a heathen. The Hebrews included in the term goim
   or nations, all the tribes of men who had not received the true
   faith,and were not circumcised. The christians translated goim by the
   L. gentes, and imitated the Jews in giving the name gentiles to all
   nations who were not Jews nor christians. In civil affairs, the
   denomination was given to all nations who were not Romans.

   GEN'TILE, a. Pertaining to pagans or heathens.
